03/09/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- The winner of the June general elections, the ruling Democratic Party (DP), signed a coalition agreement Wednesday (September 2nd) with the Socialist Movement for Integration (SMI) to govern the country over the next four years. SMI leader Ilir Meta has been named deputy prime minister and foreign minister. The SMI will also control the ministries of health and economy, and the post of deputy parliament speaker. Prime Minister Sali Berisha stressed that the goal of the coalition is to lead the country to EU membership. He added that they will work together to make the new Election Code inclusive for all. (Top Channel, Shekulli, Ora News, Klan, Alsat - 02/09/09)
